Melt the margarine with the sugars and pour over the rolls.
Lightly cover with towel and let set overnight.
In the morning, uncover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Delicious!

title: snow ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook on medium heat until thick. Pour mixture into a large bowl of clean snow.
Stir well.
Keep adding clean snow until the desired consistency of ice cream.

title: gelatin gems
directions: Add juice to gelatin.
Add water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: venison or moose cabbage rolls
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Mix in the rice, dill, salt and pepper.
Put cabbage leaves in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain and dry.
Place meat mix in middle of leaves.
Fold and secure with pick.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Earlier in the day:
Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan according to box directions.
Make 3 packages of mousse.
Use a large bowl and follow directions on back of package.

title: shells a la thom(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Prepare sauce (recipe follows) and keep warm.
Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add Ricotta and stir until melted. Add cooked pasta, turning until well coated.
Sprinkle parsley and Parmesan or Romano cheese over top and toss gently.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to platter.
Ladle some of Savory Italian Tomato Sauce over top and serve immediately.

title: corn dogs
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Blend ingredients together and dip franks into batter.
Fry about 3 minutes.

title: sweet potato surprise icing
directions: In a large thick saucepan, combine flour and sugar. Blend in slowly egg yolks and milk.
Add margarine (cut in chunks) and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching (about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat and add coconut. Beat and cool.
Spread on cake and allow to set several hours for extra moistness.

title: spiced tea punch
directions: In a large pot (4-quart) combine water, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Boil and simmer 10 minutes.
In 2-quart pot, add boiling water and tea bags.
Make tea and pour in first pot. Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes; turn the pan around at 6 minutes.

title: fresh veggie cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients except mint in a container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth; chill.
Serve with fresh mint, if desired.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs and add to dry mixture a little at a time.
Add Pet milk, sweet milk; pour in slowly vanilla.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes with celery and onion.
Combine dressing mix with water and mayonnaise.
Add to potatoes and toss to coat.

title: one loaf bread
directions: Mix water and yeast together and set for 15 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, oleo and egg; mix well.
Add enough flour to make a smooth batter.

Add 1/2 of flour at a time, until all of the flour is used, making a stiff dough (more flour can be added if needed). Pour dough out on a well floured board and knead until small blisters under surface of dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl to rise.
Cover with towel, let rise to double in size, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In
a
9 x 13-inch pan, crumble raw
ground
beef.
Add onion soup
mix and a little water.
Add	frozen	vegetables, cream of mushroom soup and 3/4 can of
water.
Mix all together.
Arrange frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Bring tomatoes and sugar to boil in saucepan, stirring constantly and boil for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add package of Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Seal in 1/2-pint jars and store in the refrigerator.

title: asparagus mushroom bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet; saute mushrooms and onion until tender (15 minutes).
Remove vegetables.
Add 3 tablespoons butter to skillet; heat until bubbly.
Combine flour, bouillon, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Stir into butter.
Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it boils; boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut asparagus spears into thirds.
Drain any liquid from mushroom mixture.
Stir asparagus, mushroom mixture and lemon juice into sauce; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven until asparagus is tender, about 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crock pot cheddar chicken
directions: Cover chicken breasts with both cans of soup (do not dilute soup).
Cook on low 6-8 hours.

title: little molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Mix molasses, soda and water, shortening, egg, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt with part of the flour.
Add sugar and sift remainder of flour and mix together with all the ingredients.
Roll into good size balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then turn temperature down to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken with onion soup, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, garlic, and 1 teaspoon cornstarch. Marinate 20 minutes.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites with a fork.
Add vanilla and sugar; beat. Fold in Ritz cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: zucchini or carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream the oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add zucchini or carrots or both (2 cups total) and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients (pineapple is optional) and beat until well combined.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: squash casserole(serves 8)
directions: Cook squash and onion in saucepan with water until tender. Drain and place in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese, salt, pepper and sugar over squash.
Add Cheese Sauce.
Top with bread crumbs. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy lumpia
directions: Fry hamburger and drain oil.
Add the shredded vegetables (coleslaw), vinegar and shoyu.
Mix and cook for a few minutes. Keep it crunchy; don't overcook.
Add garlic salt and black pepper to taste.
Let cool.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons hamburger mixture on lumpia wrapper and roll, tucking in sides before you reach the end.
Pan-fry in 1/2-inch of oil.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and other ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls and cover with nuts.

title: dump cake recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and DUMP into a Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for an hour or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool for about 10 minutes and dump firmly--like slam it down on a cutting board to get it out of the pan. Good by itself or SUPER with ice cream.

title: chalupas
directions: Cook dry pinto beans as usual.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add 1/2 small onion, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and let simmer 30 minutes.
Fry tortillas crisp in oil and drain.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in double boiler.
Beat 1 minute with electric mixer.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly, until mixture forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and beat until of spreading consistency. Will frost tops and sides of two 9-inch layers or one 10-inch tube cake.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese onto platter. Next spread cocktail sauce, then top with green onions and shrimp. Serve with crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and cut apples into small slices or small chunks. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour half of batter into a greased tube pan.
Place half of apple mixture over it, then pour in remaining batter.
Top with remaining apple mixture.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Take one can of crescent rolls and press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown in oven at 375°.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing together and spread on top of crust.
Chop vegetables and layer on top of crust/sauce mixture.
Top all with cheese and bacon bits.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch. Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown. Drain. Stir in salt and pepper. Spread in pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: festive make-ahead pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells according to package directions; rinse and drain.
Toss macaroni with oil to prevent shells sticking together. Put lettuce in one layer in a 3-quart glass or clear plastic bowl; top with cooled macaroni, then egg slices.
Sprinkle with pepper. Add in layers the ham, peas, and cheese.
Spread dressing carefully over the top to edge of bowl.
Cover tight with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Toss salad at table before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and discard.
Wash mushrooms. Stuff mushrooms with sausage.
Put in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350° or until sausage is brown.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Toss together the artichokes, tomatoes, peppers and onions. In a separate bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Serve over a bed of greens.
Yield:
25 portions.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls(golabki)
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves by scalding in boiling water to which 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt have been added.
Drain. Cool in cold water and pat dry.
Cut out heavy ribs.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine meat, egg, rice and seasoning.
Spread each leaf with about 2 tablespoons of the mixture.
Fold the two opposite sides and roll, starting with one of the open ends.
Place in pan.
Add butter and 1 cup hot water. Simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Cabbage rolls may be served with mushroom sauce, tomato sauce or sour cream.
They are more delicious if served, reheated, the next day.

title: pea salad
directions: This is one of those quick salads.
Run hot water over the peas.
Drain them & add mayonnaise a few tablespoons at a time to get the peas to stick together.
Then, you cube up some Cheddar cheese, & chop some onions & add to the peas.
Some like more cheese than onions (I do).
Mix them up & chill.

title: boiled icing(a world war ii recipe)
directions: Boil together water, vinegar and sugar until it spins a thread.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites and beat until creamy.
Add lemon juice.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and mix with spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Cook ziti noodles; drain.
Mix thoroughly in a large bowl the balance of ingredients.

title: cheesy chilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with green pepper, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce, picante, cumin and salt; simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon small amount of meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spreading to coat bottom of dish.
Top with 6 tortillas, overlapping to cover bottom of dish.
Top with half the remaining meat mixture; sprinkle with one cup of cheese. Cover with remaining tortillas, overlapping to cover cheese; top with remaining meat mixture.
Cover tightly with foil; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream surprise
directions: Early in day or up to 1 week ahead:
Place ice cream in refrigerator
to
soften
slightly,
about
30 minutes.
Chill small cookie sheet in freezer.

title: peach chutney
directions: Coarsely chop peaches.
Combine sugar, honey, vinegar and mace.
Tie cloves and cinnamon stick in cheesecloth bag.
Add to peach mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove spice bag.
Pour chutney in glass bowl and chill.
Cover.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add lemon juice to milk and set aside. Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; mix.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Add the rest of the spices, baking powder and soda; mix.
Add egg and milk, beat until smooth.
Spoon 1/2 cup of reserved mixture in the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon in batter.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: deluxe nacho platter
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter and cook onion and bell pepper over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in water, rice and Spanish sauce and cumin; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and chilies until cheese is melted.
Let cool slightly in a large round shallow broiler-proof baking dish.
Layer 1/2 each of the chips, rice mixture, tomatoes, olives and 1 cup cheese.
Repeat layering, ending with cheese.
Broil 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Top with sour cream.

title: eagle brand butterscotch logs
directions: Melt the butterscotch bits over low heat. Stir in the milk. Add the vanilla and pecans.
Shape into "large" roll and roll in powdered sugar.
When firm and cool, slice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix mayonnaise, bacon bits and minced onion together.
Spoon into mushrooms, then sprinkle cheese mixture on top and bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet, stirring over medium heat until brown.
Drain well and set aside.
Butter an 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line with crescent roll dough, pressing dough firmly into the pan.
Sprinkle the cooked sausage and the cheese over the dough and set the pan aside.

title: bavarian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes and 1/4 cup flour. Form small balls, roll in flour and brown in oil.
Add remaining flour and tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin; mix just enough to eliminate lumps.
Some will remain but should be just small ones.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken licken good pork chops
directions: Combine the flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Shake chops in mixture. Brown in oil.
Place browned chops in oven pan. Add soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan with vegetable oil.
Spread prepared apples in the bottom of the pan. Cover with lemon juice and honey.
In medium-size bowl, combine flour, oats, oil and spice.
Spread over apples and pour apple juice on top.
Bake for 35 minutes and serve.

title: scallop linguini
directions: Marinate scallops in lemon juice, parsley and garlic salt for 15 minutes.
Cook linguini according to package directions.
Saute scallops in 1/4 pound butter for 8 minutes or until done.
Add heavy cream; cook until hot.
Add linguini.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serve.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.

title: zesty nibbles
directions: Place crackers in plastic container.
Warm oil.
Add seasonings to oil.
Pour mixture over crackers and toss gently. Cover tightly and let stand for 24 hours.
Do ahead.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: play doh
directions: Cook until thick and smooth.
Store in plastic Baggie.

title: 5-minute mex-cheese snacks
directions: In
a large bowl, combine cheese and salsa. Stir until well mixed. Slice bread lengthwise.
Cover each half with cheese and salsa mixture. Broil 5 minutes or until golden brown. Add green chiles and black olives, if desired. Slice and serve immediately.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Mix thoroughly first 3 ingredients.
Stir in milk.
Sift and stir in flour, baking powder and salt;
stir in blueberries. Spread batter in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: steamed fish
directions: Place butter and lemon juice in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds until melted. Arrange fish pieces, thickest end towards outside.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Halfway through, turn fish and sprinkle with other half of salt, pepper and paprika.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Blend (with food processor if possible).
Add bananas and nuts.
Sift flour and add to mixture. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pralines
directions: Prepare ahead of time.
Cut open a brown paper bag and grease with oleo.
Make 40 to 50 small piles of pecan halves on the greased bag.
It will take 1 pint to 1 quart of pecans.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Mix next 8 ingredients well. Add noodles and last 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: french vanilla banana cream pie
directions: Place banana slices in crust.
Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Gently stir in 1 cup of the Cool Whip; spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Top pie with remaining Cool Whip.

title: great potluck vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables.
Save 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir contents of vegetable seasoning packet, margarine and water in bowl.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir until water is absorbed.
Mix soup, chicken, vegetables and thyme in 2-quart casserole.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt
margarine in pan and add flour.
Mix well and add mushroom
soup, celery soup and mushrooms; set aside, but keep warm.
Boil,
remove
from
bone,
cut
up
and
set aside the chicken.
Take
cups of the broth from the chicken and cook
rice
by using directions on box, using broth instead of water.
Use
a
casserole dish and layer the mushroom mixture, chicken and the rice.
Alternate until all is used. Put slices of cheese
on
top.
Put
in
oven long enough to melt cheese. Serves 4.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust. Top with ready crust. Pat butter on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Cool, add applesauce and dash of cinnamon.
Pour half in a long dish.
Let congeal in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery and pecans. Spread on congealed jello.
Top with remaining jello, congeal.

title: german skillet supper
directions: Brown beef in margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat 30 to 35 minutes without lifting the cover until rice is tender.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat to thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and crushed pineapple.
Set aside.

title: richard simmons' classic citrus salad
directions: To make dressing, whisk together vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt, pepper and olive oil.
To make salad, arrange remaining ingredients in serving bowl.
Pour dressing over salad.
Toss.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Beat eggs with sugar until thick.
Sift together 1/2 cup sifted flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 370° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread in a can
directions: Mix the eggs, oil and sugar and add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients together.
Grease soup cans well and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied brie
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with apples, pears, and crackers.

title: rueben casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Boil approximately 10 minutes or until fork can be easily inserted.
DO NOT cook until soft!

title: picadillo
directions: Place hamburger in large pot.
Season with garlic, oregano, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Add onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Cook over medium heat.
Chop and fold ingredients as it cooks.
(Do not stir until it is fully cooked.)
When ingredients look well cooked, add capers, olives and raisins.

title: slime(a fat free dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill and enjoy!

title: german sandwich
directions: Combine ingredients, except bread dough, and cook at low heat, stirring occasionally until done.
Drain and cool.
Roll out bread dough 3/8-inch thick; cut into rectangles, 3 x 6-inch.
Place 1/2 cup meat mixture on one end of each rectangle.
Fold over and seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: fat-free rocky road brownies
directions: Add ingredients one at a time; beat well after each addition. After adding marshmallow cream, stir just enough to create brown and white swirls.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch brownie pan lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes.

title: fettucini parmesan with vegetables
directions: Place chopped tomatoes, onion, carrot, thyme, parsley and pepper in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Add asparagus pieces to saucepan.
Pour in vinegar and simmer mixture, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add reserved tomato seeds and juice and continue cooking until most of the liquid has evaporated and asparagus is tender, about 15 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice in as little water as possible, until tender. Brown beef and onion; drain well.
Blend all ingredients except almonds.
Bake in greased casserole at 325° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix together shortening, sugar, egg, and vanilla.
Beat well, then add sour cream.
Add flour mixture until well blended.
Roll out on floured surface about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: low-fat and low-cholesterol corn bread dressing
directions: Toast bread crumbs.
In large bowl, crumble corn bread and add toasted bread crumbs.
Add onions, celery and seasonings.
Add hot broth to make a soft moist mixture.
Mix well.
Add margarine and milk; mixture should be very soft to allow for loss of moisture during baking; add more broth if necessary.
Spray 9 x 12-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.
Pour mixture in and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat and brown. Very good when eaten with maple syrup or pancake syrup.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix together in large roasting pan; cover.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: walnut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fully blended.
Slowly beat in eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend in nuts, vanilla and sour cream.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pans, then invert onto wire racks.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: Coat bottom and sides of an 8 inch pie plate lightly with butter.
Combine chocolate syrup and chocolate chips in a small microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on HIGH until hot, about 45 seconds.
Stir until smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the chocolate mixture.
Combine remaining chocolate mixture and cereal in a medium bowl and mix to coat cereal.
Press mixture over bottom and up sides of prepared pie plate.
Freeze until firm, about 15 minutes.
Combine reserved chocolate mixture and the sour cream in a small bowl and mix well.
Spread half the ice cream in the prepared pie plate.
Drizzle with half the sour cream mixture. Top with remaining ice cream and drizzle with remaining sour cream mixture.
Freeze pie, covered, until firm, about 1 hour.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix together the soups and milk in a bowl.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 inch
glass dish; layer ingredients as follows:
tortillas, chicken, cheese, chilli's, onion and half the soup mixture. Repeat.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Refrigerate overnight or for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and water.
Bring to boil until thick.
Then add Jell-O and pour over fresh raspberries in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Fresh strawberries can also be used with this recipe.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover until chicken
starts to separate from the bone, about 30 minutes. Remove chicken from broth; shred and set aside. Saute onion,
garlic and cumin in oil. Add green chilies and saute. Add beans, onion mixture and spices to chicken broth and simmer 1 hour. Add chicken and 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese. Serve with remaining cheese.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together. Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs. Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Stir in the flour mixture.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Poke holes on top of the batter with a fork.
Sprinkle top of batter with a mixture of 1/8 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Turn pan on side to cool. Yields 1 loaf.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well to combine all flavors.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Add chopped nuts. Grease Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon or more of sugar in bottom of pan. Sprinkle a few nuts on the sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can add coconut to this cake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Reserve a few French fried onions to add later.
Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining onions on top.
Leave uncovered. Bake another 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: choconut caramel bars
directions: Melt choc. chips and shortening.
Stir until mixture is smooth. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into an 8 in. foil lined square pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (15 min.).
Melt caramels, butter and water.
Stir until caramels melt and mixture is smooth; stir in nuts until well blended.
Pour into choc. lined pan.
Spread evenly and refrigerate until tacky (15 min.).
Top with remaining choc. (Re-heat if necessary.) Spread evenly to cover caramel filling. Return to refrigerator and chill until firm (1 hour).
Cut into 1 by 2 in. rectangles.
Keep refrigerated.

title: farmer's salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a covered container.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Yield:
7 cups.
Makes 9 servings.

title: maude rutley's fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients for crust with a fork.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well, then divide the dough in half.
Tear 2 sheets of waxed paper as large as your cookie sheet.
Roll
1/2 of the dough between the two sheets.
Fit rolled dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mom's donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill dough at least 1 hour. Fry in hot Crisco oil.
Sugar while warm.

title: chops and dumplings
directions: Brown meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion on top and water.
Cover skillet; simmer until tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 1 1/2 to 3 cups water.
Meanwhile, make dumplings.
Stir milk and flour, only until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot meat (not in the liquid).
Cook 10 minutes uncovered, then cover tightly and cook 10 minutes longer.
Thicken liquid with flour for gravy.

title: apple pie in bag
directions: You will need one large cooking bag (20 x 14-inch) with nylon tie.
Prepare pie crust mix as directed for 9-inch pie crust. Line pie plate with high fluted edges.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In large bowl, toss apples, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Fill pie shell with mixture; pile high in center.
In small bowl with hands, knead butter, remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour into soft dough.
Pull dough into small pieces; flatten each slightly and arrange on top of apple mixture.
It is not necessary to completely cover apple mixture. Insert several wood skewers (4-inch tall)* so bag will not touch top of pie while baking.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pie in bag; close with nylon tie.
Cut 6 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Place on cookie sheet.
Set on center rack.
Be sure bag does not touch oven sides, racks or walls.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown. Remove from oven.
With shears, cut bag open.
Take out pie; bottom of pan will be greasy.
Sit on wire rack to cool.
Serves 8.

title: simple potato dish
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Place on heavy-duty foil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and soup mix.
Dot with butter. Seal foil well. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chewy pecan brownies
directions: Melt oleo and sugar together in saucepan.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour and cocoa; add pecans.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, careful not to overbake.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease muffin cups.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in flour, milk and salt, just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill cups about 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes; decrease oven temperature to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.
Immediately remove from cups and serve hot.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix eggs, apples, lemon juice, vanilla and oil together until mixed well.
Add the rest of the ingredients until all are combined well.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for about 40 minutes.
Cut and serve
when cool.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: calzones
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Coat a baking sheet with a nonstick spray. Unroll pizza crust on a cutting board and stretch dough into a 12-inch square. Cut in quarters (you'll have four 6-inch squares).

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and mix until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended, then chips and nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut, when cool, into 36 bars.

title: chicken breast
directions: Layer chicken (uncooked).
Cover with cheese; add soup and cover with Stove Top dressing (cooked).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes with foil.
Remove foil; bake 20 minutes until brown.

title: zucchini-raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beat well. Stir in zucchini.
Set aside.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These cookies can be frozen for later. Yields 3 dozen.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Set oven at 300°.
Mix first 5 items.
Spread on rolls and cut in half.
Put cheese and ham in rolls.
Bake 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add them alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into paper-lined 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until straw inserted into center of cake comes out clean.

title: egg white meringue
directions: Add a little cold water to cornstarch to make a paste.
Stir into boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt, then sugar gradually.
Beat in cold cornstarch.
Put on pie.
Brown in oven.

title: delicious cranberry salad
directions: Grind up cranberries.
Mix with apples.
Add sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add whipped cream, marshmallows and chopped nuts. Mix all together.
Pour into glass baking dish or casserole and freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in a small amount of water until tender. Drain well.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Add additional ingredients except egg whites.
Stir.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into squash mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dobbin
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
May be used as dessert or salad.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream and blend well the shortening, sugar, honey and egg. Mix and stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll thin and cut.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Ice cookies.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set until jelled.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, lard and molasses well with mixer.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Roll in ball size of walnut.
Dip first in water, then in sugar.
Place sugar-side up on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Chill for 30 minutes in icebox.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crumble up Oreo cookies.
Melt butter.
Add cookies to butter in long cake pan, making a crust.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Blend in butter with fingertips until well mixed.
Pat evenly into bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat well.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese. Then add strawberries and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: jessie's bundt cake
directions: Grease a tube pan and flour.
Combine cake mix, dry pudding, oil, water and eggs.
Mix well for about 8 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Pour batter in pan alternately with layer of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 8 minutes.
Ice cake while warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dream squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooked cookie mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy peanut butter  pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in the whipped topping. Coarsely chop half of the peanut butter cups; stir into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Quarter remaining peanut butter cups; arrange over top.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: chess pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg together with hands.
Press into greased oblong pan.

title: budget beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in hot oil.
Place uncooked noodles on top of meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the noodles. Do not stir.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Serves 6.

title: russian cabbage
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until slightly brown. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Put half of cabbage in greased casserole.
Alternate layers with tomato mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ummm good!

title: texas trash
directions: The Lord is my Shepherd I shall not want.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters, if desired.
Freeze on cookie sheet for an hour. Cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cooked chocolate fudge icing
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook one minute more.
Add vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Beat with a mixer until thick or stands at a peak.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash potatoes and mix all ingredients together.
Beat until light and frothy.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine all the ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Add brown sugar, spices and eggs.
Beat 1 minute.
Add apples; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Mix with pastry cutter or by hand:
cheese, butter and dry ingredients.
Add water slowly, just enough to hold the dough together.
Roll out part of the dough on a floured board.
The dough should be as thin as a pie crust. Cut into strips.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 15 minutes or until strips are lightly brown.
Good with salads or snacks.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients. Pour half of mixture in a dish and let congeal. After this has congealed, spread one cup sour cream over this. Then pour other half of mixture and let congeal.

title: swede cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a tubular shape.
Refrigerate until stiff.
Cut into slices and bake at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix and top with Velveeta slices or strips.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple; fold in cubes.
Turn in 2 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: layered avocado dip
directions: Smash avocados in an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Cover avocados with sour cream.
Pour taco sauce over sour cream, just enough to cover sour cream.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top. Refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: spanish potato omelet
directions: Heat oils in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add potatoes to hot oil. Turn with spatula several times to coat all slices with oil.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add peanut butter, sugar and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Please use 1 large bowl.
Mix marshmallows and sour cream together.
Then add mandarin oranges (chopped up) and crushed pineapple.
Drain the juices first.
Then mix together with large can of peaches (chopped up and drained of juices).
Mix all together.
On top put coconut, walnuts and red cherries.

title: company chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between two pieces of wax paper and flatten to 1/4 inch using rolling pin or meat mallet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix in bowl, add eggs, applesauce, salt, flavoring.
Beat 3 minutes.

title: no-fry french fries
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil. Spray with vegetable cooking spray. Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch wide slices.
Toss potatoes with oil, garlic, salt and pepper to coat well. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, tossing once or twice, until potatoes are crisp and golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes, onion and garlic.
(I use a blender.) Combine all ingredients in bowl, stirring in egg, flour and seasonings.
Use approximately 1/3 cup batter per pancake.
Fry in skillet on medium-high temperature until edges are firm and starting to brown.
Turn over and repeat on other side. Serve with butter, sour cream or applesauce.
Makes 8 to 10 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Put aside 1/4 cup noodles.
Combine remaining noodles, soup, water, seafood, celery, water chestnuts and half the almonds.
Put into a casserole.
Top with remaining noodles and almonds.
Bake uncovered 370° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dunbutter biscuits
directions: Mix together; pour into muffin pan (ungreased).
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add can of French fried onions (less 1/2 cup) and can of mushrooms.
Put in ungreased 2 1/2 to 3 quart casserole.
Heat can of mushroom soup (undiluted) to a boil. Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over meat in casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Cut biscuits in half and edge casserole with cut side down.
Mix egg, 1/2 cup sour cream, salt and celery seed; pour over biscuits and across top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
